Class DoubleThing

java.lang.Object
  org.hecl.DoubleThing
All Implemented Interfaces:
RealThing
public class DoubleThing
extends java.lang.Object
implements RealThing

The DoubleThing class represents a Thing that contains either a floating point or large number.

Version:
1.0
Author:
David N. Welton

promote

public static double promote(Thing t)
                      throws HeclException
The promote method takes a thing and promotes it to a double in some way or another. If it's a double or an int, we don't do anything. If it's something else, we attempt to transform it into either an a double, or if it is an integer, into an integer.

Parameters:
t - a Thing value
Returns:
a double value
Throws:
HeclException - if an error occurs
